 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/7044/how-to-increase-font-size-default-terminal/?answer=7406#post-id-7406</link><description>In the terminal that comes with most distros you would be able to access your preferences menu which is most certainly either somewhere in the menu options on top of your terminal or entered by right clicking and selecting preferences or profile.

May I suggest you also select a nicer font than most distros include by default as well.

Some nice ones include these
https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts

Previews of these fonts and many others can be found at 
https://www.google.com/fonts

It is usually sufficient to drop custom font dirs into ~/.fonts but follow directions for your distro</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Nov 2015 09:07:21 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/7044/how-to-increase-font-size-default-terminal/?answer=7406#post-id-7406</guid></item><item><title>Answer by a93ushakov for &lt;p&gt;Hello!&lt;/p&gt;

